HEADWORD: Triolet
<hw>Tri"o*let</hw> <pr>(tr⟦imac⟧"⟦osl⟧*l⟦ecr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>triolet</ets>. See <er>Trio</er>.]</ety> <def>A short poem
or stanza of eight lines, in which the first line is repeated as the
fourth and again as the seventh line, the second being, repeated as the
eighth.</def> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

